<s docid="FT931-3764" num="4" wdcount="21"> FT 13 MAR 93 / Bombay blasts leave 200 
dead: Federal troops flown in after wave of bombings on commercial targets</s>
<s docid="FT931-3764" num="6" wdcount="31"> THE INDIAN government flew federal 
paramilitary troops into Bombay last night after more than a dozen bombs 
exploded in the city, killing about 200 people and injuring more than a 
thousand.</s>
<s docid="FT931-3764" num="10" wdcount="33"> The identity of the bombers was unknown, 
but the attacks were a severe setback to India's attempts to heal the wounds 
created by recent intercommunal violence, which has caused deep shock throughout 
India.</s>
